<div class="page-header"><h1>ACC is where electricians, nurses, and welders get trained</h1>
<p>Community college is not just about degrees. ACC offers certificates you can complete in under a year, apprenticeship pathways, and workforce training that leads directly to employment. Pflugerville residents pay 3.4x more for all of it.</p></div>

<div class="prose">
<h2>Programs that lead to jobs</h2>
<p>ACC offers more than 100 programs in 10 areas of study. Here are the ones most relevant to Pflugerville's workforce needs:</p>

<div class="card-grid" style="margin:var(--space-lg) 0;">
<div class="card"><h3>Construction and skilled trades</h3><p>Welding, HVAC, plumbing, electrical, construction technology. A welding certificate (approximately 30 credit hours) costs <strong class="text-teal">$2,550 in-district</strong> vs. $8,580 out-of-district. PfISD already runs construction Career Academies with electrical and plumbing apprenticeships.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>Healthcare</h3><p>Nursing (through BSN), vocational nursing, medical lab technology, diagnostic imaging, occupational therapy assistant, phlebotomy. ACC's nursing program is one of the largest in central Texas. Median RN salary in Austin: $78,000+.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>Technology</h3><p>Cybersecurity, computer programming, networking, web development. A cybersecurity certificate costs approximately $2,040 in-district vs. $6,864 out-of-district. Median info security analyst salary in Austin: $100,000+.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>Advanced manufacturing</h3><p>ACC's Advanced Manufacturing Production training is expanding nationally through semiconductor industry partnerships. PfISD's new CTE center (opening 2027) will create local infrastructure for manufacturing training pathways.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>Business and entrepreneurship</h3><p>Small business development, accounting, logistics and supply chain, fashion marketing, culinary arts. ACC provides customized workforce training for local employers and small business resources.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>Public service</h3><p>Criminal justice, fire science, emergency medical services. These programs feed directly into local government and first-responder hiring pipelines.</p></div>
</div>

